exif:ImageDescription: WAR STORIES...Marthe Cohn relates her experience gathering information behind enemy lines during World War II. At 95, Marthe Cohn remembers clearly her life as a Jewish spy during World War II. When the French military discovered that Cohn, a blond, light-eyed woman, spoke fluent German, she was recruited into the French intelligence service and trained to gain information that would help the French defeat the Nazis.
